  "title": "Feat/multi index results",
  "body": "Hi team!\r\n\r\nThis PR is addressing the multi index feature in a simple way, it allows to display results from different Algolia indices. This would be useful to create a similar experience as autocomplete.js for instance.\r\n\r\n**How it works?**\r\n\r\n1. The connector is creating derived helpers from the original one\r\n2. When results are retrieved by any helper a render is requested\r\n\r\n**What is missing?**\r\n\r\n* [ ] Better templating option\r\n* [x] Allow `escapeHits` option like `Hits` widget\r\n* [ ] Allow `transformData` scoped to any index\r\n* [ ] Tests\r\n\r\nI'm also not fan of the naming, I do not have any strong opinion on it, any help would be appreciated 👍 ",
